    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">What &ldquo;after-hours help&rdquo; actually means here.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>We want to be honest about this, because the internet is full of &ldquo;24/7 QuickBooks support&rdquo; lines that aren&rsquo;t what they claim. TechBrot is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm with <strong>normal business hours &mdash; Monday&ndash;Friday, roughly 8am&ndash;6pm ET</strong>. We are not a 24/7 call center, there is no overnight phone bank, and we won&rsquo;t pretend otherwise. If you reach us at 11pm, a person isn&rsquo;t going to pick up the phone.</p>
      <p>What you <em>can</em> do after hours is start the work without waiting for the office to open. Submit the free file review, fill out the discovery brief, or leave a message tonight, and it&rsquo;s in the queue the moment we&rsquo;re back &mdash; a Certified ProAdvisor reviews it and responds the next business day, prioritizing urgent file and books problems first. The honest promise is momentum and a fast next-business-day response, not an instant or overnight one. And if what you actually need is an Intuit account, login, subscription, billing, or software-bug fix, that&rsquo;s Intuit&rsquo;s to resolve &mdash; Intuit publishes its own support availability, which we don&rsquo;t control or speak for.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

